'''''Les voyages aventureux du Capitaine Martin de Hoyarsabal, habitant du Cubiburu, contenant les règles et enseignments nécessaires à la bonne et seure navigation''''' is a treatise on navigation by [[Martin de Hoyarçabal]],<ref name="Halimi2008"/> from the [[French Basque Country]].<ref name="LitalienPalomino2007">{{cite book|author1=Raymonde Litalien|author2=Jean-François Palomino|author3=Denis Vaugeois|title=La mesure d'un continent: atlas historique de l'Amérique du Nord, 1492-1814|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WJqZOMlZSN0C&pg=PA121|year=2007|publisher=Presses Paris Sorbonne|isbn=978-2-84050-550-1|page=121}}</ref> It was published in 1547 in [[Bordeaux]], edited by [[Jean Chouin]]. It was the world's first pedagogical book on navigation, whose purpose was to teach sailors how to sail.<ref name="Halimi2008">{{cite book|author=Suzy Halimi|title=La nuit dans l'Angleterre des Lumières|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hSPtNC-zrbMC&pg=PA58|year=2008|publisher=Presses Sorbonne Nouvelle|isbn=978-2-87854-424-4|page=58}}</ref>

